      "opacity": 100,
      "text": "Non-Functional Requirements",
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlignment": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "version": 296,
      "versionNonce": 2017513726,
      "index": "b0C",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "seed": 482867582,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781653036896,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "originalText": "Non-Functional Requirements",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.3333333333333333
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "NIboKAQeC-V48lVgJdfHu",
      "x": -205.08967389735096,
      "y": -30.792597108738278,
      "width": 579.1363525390625,
      "height": 624,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "text": "NFR1 — GPU-First\n  Use GPU when available; gracefully fall back to CPU.\n  ▎ Exception: Diarize currently forced CPU (speechbrain MPS upstream bug)\nNFR2 — Always-On Access\n  Processed results queryable at any time; full-text search across all files.\nNFR3 — No SPOF\n  Each service component must tolerate individual failure without total system loss.\n  ▎ Current risk: Redis single instance, SQLite single file — needs mitigation design\nNFR4 — Scale-Out Ready\n  API/Web layer designed for horizontal scaling.\n  Current throughput bounded by single Mac mini; max concurrent pipeline runs configurable.\nNFR5 — Future Multi-User Extensible\n  Architecture must not preclude adding auth / user management later.\n  Not implemented now; single-user tool in current phase.\nNFR6 — Configurability \n  Per-job feature toggles (diarization, output format, sensitivity).\n  Global defaults in config.yaml; retry count configurable.\n",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlignment": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "version": 504,
      "versionNonce": 398802402,
      "index": "b0D",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "seed": 1858607550,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781653071336,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "originalText": "NFR1 — GPU-First\n  Use GPU when available; gracefully fall back to CPU.\n  ▎ Exception: Diarize currently forced CPU (speechbrain MPS upstream bug)\nNFR2 — Always-On Access\n  Processed results queryable at any time; full-text search across all files.\nNFR3 — No SPOF\n  Each service component must tolerate individual failure without total system loss.\n  ▎ Current risk: Redis single instance, SQLite single file — needs mitigation design\nNFR4 — Scale-Out Ready\n  API/Web layer designed for horizontal scaling.\n  Current throughput bounded by single Mac mini; max concurrent pipeline runs configurable.\nNFR5 — Future Multi-User Extensible\n  Architecture must not preclude adding auth / user management later.\n  Not implemented now; single-user tool in current phase.\nNFR6 — Configurability \n  Per-job feature toggles (diarization, output format, sensitivity).\n  Global defaults in config.yaml; retry count configurable.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 2.6666666666666665
    },
